The paper discusses a new concept called Wikiometrics, which involves deriving metrics and indicators from Wikipedia. This concept is related to several sub-categories of computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), computers and society (cs.CY), and sound (cs.SD). The paper specifically applies the Wikiometrics concept to ranking world universities and academic journals, which suggests a focus on information retrieval and social and information networks. Therefore, cs.DL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.SI, cs.CY, and cs.SD.
